    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and quarter your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Separate the <strong>white fat</strong> and the <strong>duck</strong> <strong>jelly</strong> from your <strong>duck legs </strong>and reserve for later</p><p>Add the <strong>shallot quarters </strong>and <strong>thyme</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and top with the <strong>duck legs</strong> and a<strong> </strong>pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the duck is cooking, cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces and lightly crush your <strong>garlic </strong>(removing the skin)</p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>and <strong>crushed garlic </strong>to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>orange[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Cut the <strong>zested orange</strong> in half</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>piece[s] of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A3 paper</p><p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to the middle with your <strong>flaked almonds</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the broccoli to form a sealed parcel[s] per person then add to a separate baking tray</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the duck has been in the oven for 20 min, put the <strong>broccoli parcel[s]</strong> in the oven for 10-12 min or until tender \u2013 this is your <strong>buttered broccoli & flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, heat a pot over a medium-high heat with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and cook for 2 min, stirring often or until the sugar has fully dissolved</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>cornflour </strong>in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Once the sugar has dissolved, reduce the heat to medium and add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>orange zest</strong>, <strong>chicken stock </strong>and the juice of the <strong>orange halves</strong></p><p>Sir through the <strong>cornflour </strong>and continue cooking for 8-9 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>orange sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with the <strong>duck fat </strong>and <strong>jelly</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>garlicky duck fat mash</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of milk if your mash is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-a-l-orange-with-garlicky-duck-fat-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlicky duck fat mash </strong>and top with the <strong>cooked duck legs</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>buttered broccoli & flaked almonds </strong>to the side and drizzle over the <strong>orange sauce</strong></p><p>Season with a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
